[SN]TITLE[SN]
Enfield pensioner robbed at gunpoint

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pensioner has been robbed at gunpoint in her home by three men in what police are calling a "cowardly and callous" attack.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The victim, in her 70s, was alone at her home in Lancaster Road, Enfield, when she answered the door.
She was confronted by three men, one holding a handgun, who pushed her inside and forced her to hand over Â£200 cash.
The three men were described as white and aged in their 30s or 40s.
